HEADWORD: Mohammedism
<hw>Mo*ham"med*ism</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>The religion, or doctrines and
precepts, of <persfn>Mohammed</persfn>, contained in the
<book>Koran</book>; Islamism; Islam. The term <altname>Islam</altname>
is preferred by most Moslems, and some find the term
<ex>Mohammedanism</ex> to be offensive, as they worship
<persfn>Allah</persfn>, not <persfn>Mohammed</persfn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

